1
00:00:18,679 --> 00:00:19,960
You know what this is?

2
00:00:20,920 --> 00:00:22,960
That's right. Cash.

3
00:00:24,399 --> 00:00:26,079
Wondering where it came from?

4
00:00:26,839 --> 00:00:29,640
It fell right out of that wall.

5
00:00:31,120 --> 00:00:33,399
A full thirty million.

6
00:00:36,759 --> 00:00:39,159
I can't believe something this lucky

7
00:00:39,359 --> 00:00:41,359
actually happened to me.

8
00:00:42,079 --> 00:00:43,200
This has to be heaven's way

9
00:00:43,200 --> 00:00:44,159
of rewarding me.

10
00:00:44,600 --> 00:00:46,719
I never knew thirty million yuan

11
00:00:46,880 --> 00:00:47,920
could be this much,

12
00:00:48,119 --> 00:00:49,119
and this heavy.

13
00:00:49,920 --> 00:00:53,960
But I was still hauling it around
with the biggest grin on my face.

14
00:00:55,159 --> 00:00:55,799
From that moment on,

15
00:00:56,079 --> 00:00:58,240
I finally got to live
the life I'd always dreamed of,

16
00:00:58,640 --> 00:01:00,560
a life of pure luxury.

17
00:01:01,240 --> 00:01:03,039
Feels great, doesn't it?

18
00:01:03,960 --> 00:01:05,359
But just three days earlier,

19
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:07,359
I was nothing more than

20
00:01:07,640 --> 00:01:09,159
a miserable rat
everyone wanted to crush.

21
00:02:28,320 --> 00:02:32,180
=Wonder Wall=

22
00:02:32,240 --> 00:02:35,140
=Episode 1=

23
00:02:35,400 --> 00:02:36,080
Liar!

24
00:02:36,400 --> 00:02:37,599
You scumbag!

25
00:02:37,840 --> 00:02:39,360
You heartless piece of trash!

26
00:02:39,360 --> 00:02:40,080
You're selling fakes!

27
00:02:40,080 --> 00:02:40,599
You trash!

28
00:02:40,599 --> 00:02:41,120
You punk!

29
00:02:41,719 --> 00:02:42,879
Fraud! You're a fraud!

30
00:02:43,000 --> 00:02:44,000
You think you can hide?

31
00:02:44,039 --> 00:02:45,000
Not a chance!

32
00:02:45,080 --> 00:02:46,800
I didn't spend years dancing
in the square for nothing!

33
00:02:46,919 --> 00:02:47,719
Cut the crap!

34
00:02:47,719 --> 00:02:48,439
Look at my face!

35
00:02:48,439 --> 00:02:49,120
Just wait!

36
00:02:49,120 --> 00:02:50,430
I'll smear thisall over your face!

37
00:02:50,439 --> 00:02:51,199
Is this you?

38
00:02:51,240 --> 00:02:52,560
Is this you or not?

39
00:02:52,719 --> 00:02:54,639
Three strokes on the left,
three strokes on the right.

40
00:02:54,680 --> 00:02:56,199
Remember, three each time.

41
00:02:56,240 --> 00:02:57,280
one, two, three,

42
00:02:57,280 --> 00:02:58,719
three strokes are all you need.

43
00:02:58,719 --> 00:02:59,439
Listen...

44
00:02:59,439 --> 00:03:00,039
Only 120 yuan

45
00:03:00,080 --> 00:03:00,800
a bag.

46
00:03:00,800 --> 00:03:01,360
One bag isn't enough.

47
00:03:01,400 --> 00:03:02,120
Two bags.

48
00:03:02,159 --> 00:03:02,960
No, make that four bags.

49
00:03:03,000 --> 00:03:04,639
And I'll even throw in a free jar

50
00:03:04,680 --> 00:03:06,199
of genuine hand-ground pearl powder.

51
00:03:06,240 --> 00:03:08,000
It'll give you flawless skin

52
00:03:08,039 --> 00:03:09,319
and turn you into

53
00:03:09,360 --> 00:03:11,120
a real-life Snow White.

54
00:03:11,479 --> 00:03:12,960
Look at this Snow White face of mine!

55
00:03:12,960 --> 00:03:14,159
Do I still look like Snow White?

56
00:03:14,159 --> 00:03:15,120
How should I face my husband?

57
00:03:15,120 --> 00:03:15,919
This pearl powder

58
00:03:16,159 --> 00:03:17,759
is like a lump of mud!

59
00:03:17,840 --> 00:03:18,520
You brat!

60
00:03:18,800 --> 00:03:19,800
Idiot!

61
00:03:20,080 --> 00:03:20,919
Short-lived troublemaker!

62
00:03:21,599 --> 00:03:22,439
If you don't compensate us,

63
00:03:22,680 --> 00:03:23,520
we're calling the police!

64
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:25,199
The police will stand up for us!

65
00:03:25,520 --> 00:03:26,560
Always first in line for meals,

66
00:03:26,680 --> 00:03:27,800
always hiding when it's time to act.

67
00:03:27,840 --> 00:03:28,680
No money,

68
00:03:28,680 --> 00:03:29,319
but plenty of tricks.

69
00:03:29,599 --> 00:03:30,120
It's you!

70
00:03:30,120 --> 00:03:31,199
Is this you?

71
00:03:31,240 --> 00:03:32,080
Is it you?

72
00:03:32,240 --> 00:03:33,639
Is it you or not?

73
00:03:33,879 --> 00:03:34,719
How could it make us flawless?

74
00:03:34,719 --> 00:03:36,080
Look at my face! It's red as a tomato!

75
00:03:36,080 --> 00:03:37,680
Let me handle this. Talk to me.

76
00:03:43,520 --> 00:03:44,800
Yitong, go inside and check out.

77
00:03:45,919 --> 00:03:46,719
She'll be responsible?

78
00:03:51,400 --> 00:03:52,400
Alright. Listen to me.

79
00:03:53,039 --> 00:03:53,680
Tenfold refund.

80
00:03:53,680 --> 00:03:54,280
1,200 per person.

81
00:03:54,280 --> 00:03:55,039
12,000 for ten people.

82
00:03:55,039 --> 00:03:55,639
Any objections?

83
00:03:55,719 --> 00:03:57,159
- Yes!
- Yes!

84
00:03:57,280 --> 00:03:58,240
What about our faces?

85
00:03:58,319 --> 00:03:59,400
That's right, we need medical exams too!

86
00:03:59,560 --> 00:04:00,840
That's right, we need medical exams too!

87
00:04:00,919 --> 00:04:01,879
Facial allergies.

88
00:04:01,879 --> 00:04:03,240
Why do you need medical exams?

89
00:04:03,240 --> 00:04:04,319
I really don't get it.

90
00:04:04,360 --> 00:04:05,319
Can you stop talking for a second?

91
00:04:06,039 --> 00:04:06,919
Medical. Exams.

92
00:04:06,919 --> 00:04:07,479
Medical exams.

93
00:04:07,479 --> 00:04:08,319
That's 1,360 per person.

94
00:04:08,319 --> 00:04:09,120
For ten people, that's 13,600.

95
00:04:09,159 --> 00:04:09,879
Any objections?

96
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:11,240
- Yes!
- Yes!

97
00:04:12,439 --> 00:04:13,319
We want medical checkups.

98
00:04:13,400 --> 00:04:14,400
Or we'll call the police.

99
00:04:14,439 --> 00:04:15,039
The police decides

100
00:04:15,039 --> 00:04:15,759
who is responsible

101
00:04:15,840 --> 00:04:16,560
for this.

102
00:04:16,560 --> 00:04:17,759
You've trashed my shop,

103
00:04:17,920 --> 00:04:18,839
you've beaten him up,

104
00:04:18,839 --> 00:04:19,680
and you've messed these up.

105
00:04:19,759 --> 00:04:21,120
When the police arrive,
we'll sort it all out.

106
00:04:21,199 --> 00:04:21,680
Otherwise,

107
00:04:21,680 --> 00:04:22,519
nobody leaves this place.

108
00:04:22,600 --> 00:04:23,360
But we can pay you with

109
00:04:23,360 --> 00:04:23,839
tenfold refund.

110
00:04:23,839 --> 00:04:24,560
We mean it.

111
00:04:24,759 --> 00:04:25,160
Okay?

112
00:04:25,680 --> 00:04:26,439
Well...

113
00:04:26,439 --> 00:04:27,879
Well then, let's not bother the police.

114
00:04:28,000 --> 00:04:28,920
Just pay us already.

115
00:04:29,160 --> 00:04:30,040
Then I want compensation too.

116
00:04:30,040 --> 00:04:30,839
That backdrop wall of mine

117
00:04:30,839 --> 00:04:31,879
cost 3,200 yuan!

118
00:04:31,879 --> 00:04:32,560
Can you just shut up?

119
00:04:35,040 --> 00:04:36,839
They said livestreaming was the future.

120
00:04:36,879 --> 00:04:37,360
Someday,

121
00:04:37,360 --> 00:04:38,319
it would be huge.

122
00:04:38,319 --> 00:04:39,360
So I wanted to give it a try.

123
00:04:39,360 --> 00:04:40,079
I thought Wenwen

124
00:04:40,079 --> 00:04:41,360
would need tuition money too.

125
00:04:41,439 --> 00:04:42,800
I just wanted
to help out.

126
00:04:42,920 --> 00:04:44,040
I never expected...

127
00:04:44,160 --> 00:04:44,800
Let me ask you.

128
00:04:45,160 --> 00:04:46,319
How many people were in your channel?

129
00:04:46,360 --> 00:04:47,079
Five?

130
00:04:47,240 --> 00:04:47,639
Four.

131
00:04:47,800 --> 00:04:48,279
Did anyone

132
00:04:48,279 --> 00:04:49,199
buy your pearl powder?

133
00:04:49,480 --> 00:04:50,279
I made one sale

134
00:04:50,319 --> 00:04:51,199
to those people just now.

135
00:04:51,199 --> 00:04:52,759
If your crappy pearl powder

136
00:04:53,079 --> 00:04:53,680
can get me

137
00:04:53,680 --> 00:04:54,560
even a power strip

138
00:04:54,560 --> 00:04:55,360
I'll be impressed.

139
00:04:55,399 --> 00:04:56,519
Look at the mess you've caused.

140
00:04:56,759 --> 00:04:57,240
How much is it?

141
00:04:57,439 --> 00:04:58,040
Yu Ming, how much?

142
00:04:58,360 --> 00:04:59,639
25,672 yuan.

143
00:04:59,680 --> 00:05:00,319
Do you think we have

144
00:05:00,319 --> 00:05:01,199
that money lying around,

145
00:05:01,199 --> 00:05:01,759
Yu Ming?

146
00:05:02,439 --> 00:05:03,360
I'd rather kick you to death.

147
00:05:03,399 --> 00:05:04,199
Stop following me!

148
00:05:15,000 --> 00:05:15,920
What am I, a workhorse?

149
00:05:16,000 --> 00:05:17,160
Am I your family's workhorse?

150
00:05:17,160 --> 00:05:18,000
I've been busting my back

151
00:05:18,000 --> 00:05:18,639
dragging this family

152
00:05:18,680 --> 00:05:19,560
forward step by step.

153
00:05:19,560 --> 00:05:20,240
You think it's easy?

154
00:05:20,319 --> 00:05:21,680
Have I ever spent a dime on myself?

155
00:05:21,759 --> 00:05:22,360
Look down.

156
00:05:22,360 --> 00:05:23,160
Look at my shoes.

157
00:05:23,199 --> 00:05:24,079
They cost only 58 yuan.

158
00:05:24,120 --> 00:05:25,120
Look how worn out they are.

159
00:05:25,160 --> 00:05:26,759
Look at them.
How can you not feel guilty?

160
00:05:27,800 --> 00:05:29,040
Come on, don't be mad.

161
00:05:29,079 --> 00:05:29,519
Get lost!

162
00:05:41,800 --> 00:05:42,759
Just get lost!

163
00:05:46,680 --> 00:05:49,240
(Luzhou city, Minnan)

164
00:05:49,240 --> 00:05:49,600
(Luzhou city, Minnan)
Jia.

165
00:05:50,839 --> 00:05:52,199
Yu Ming is driving me crazy.

166
00:05:52,319 --> 00:05:53,240
I'm sick over it.

167
00:05:54,040 --> 00:05:54,720
Slow down.

168
00:05:55,079 --> 00:05:55,759
Hello, Ms. Pang.

169
00:05:55,759 --> 00:05:56,519
Seriously,

170
00:05:56,519 --> 00:05:56,879
Take it easy.

171
00:05:56,879 --> 00:05:57,759
I'm falling apart.

172
00:05:59,439 --> 00:06:00,680
Right now, on the ferry,

173
00:06:00,720 --> 00:06:02,040
I'm honestly thinking

174
00:06:02,680 --> 00:06:03,800
about throwing myself overboard.

175
00:06:04,759 --> 00:06:06,040
No one can make me better.

176
00:06:07,319 --> 00:06:08,480
Who could possibly make me better?

177
00:06:08,759 --> 00:06:09,720
If I go to therapy,

178
00:06:09,720 --> 00:06:10,639
doesn't that cost money too?

179
00:06:10,720 --> 00:06:11,680
Right now, I don't even

180
00:06:12,000 --> 00:06:14,120
have the money to see a therapist.

181
00:06:14,199 --> 00:06:15,600
I'm depressed, Jia.

182
00:06:16,360 --> 00:06:17,560
I don't think I'm ever getting better.

183
00:06:18,360 --> 00:06:19,639
And today, Yu Ming cost me

184
00:06:19,680 --> 00:06:21,040
another 26,000 yuan.

185
00:06:22,839 --> 00:06:25,199
Where am I supposed to get that money?

186
00:06:25,519 --> 00:06:26,000
I understand.

187
00:06:26,720 --> 00:06:27,680
I know you're feeling

188
00:06:27,680 --> 00:06:28,680
awful right now.

189
00:06:28,920 --> 00:06:30,360
But all this
running around Yu Ming does,

190
00:06:30,639 --> 00:06:31,959
deep down, he's
just trying to shoulder

191
00:06:31,959 --> 00:06:33,120
his share of the responsibility.

192
00:06:33,759 --> 00:06:35,199
He wants you to have a better life.

193
00:06:35,279 --> 00:06:36,399
He wants to ease your burden.

194
00:06:36,480 --> 00:06:37,560
His intentions are good.

195
00:06:37,680 --> 00:06:39,040
How is he easing my burden?

196
00:06:39,120 --> 00:06:39,879
I have to leave him.

197
00:06:39,959 --> 00:06:41,040
Then I won't have any burden at all.

198
00:06:41,639 --> 00:06:43,399
I can't take this for another minute.

199
00:06:43,519 --> 00:06:44,839
I just want to leave him.

200
00:06:46,160 --> 00:06:47,600
I can't live like this anymore.

201
00:06:48,680 --> 00:06:50,120
As long as I'm not with him,

202
00:06:50,160 --> 00:06:51,360
my life will be better no matter what.

203
00:06:52,120 --> 00:06:52,800
Business has always

204
00:06:52,800 --> 00:06:53,920
been outside his comfort zone.

205
00:06:54,240 --> 00:06:55,120
Failure is normal.

206
00:06:55,879 --> 00:06:57,079
You need to give him a little more room.

207
00:06:57,079 --> 00:06:58,160
Give him a chance to make mistakes.

208
00:06:58,279 --> 00:06:58,680
Right?

209
00:07:00,000 --> 00:07:00,800
People who lack confidence

210
00:07:00,879 --> 00:07:01,639
often struggle to

211
00:07:01,680 --> 00:07:02,959
build a good life for themselves.

212
00:07:05,000 --> 00:07:05,959
His brother's death

213
00:07:06,120 --> 00:07:07,920
left him with deep emotional scars.

214
00:07:08,360 --> 00:07:09,639
Since then, he's been distracted

215
00:07:09,680 --> 00:07:10,639
and absent-minded.

216
00:07:11,120 --> 00:07:12,000
Really, he just wants

217
00:07:12,000 --> 00:07:13,279
to do more for this family.

218
00:07:13,519 --> 00:07:14,959
Ever since college,

219
00:07:16,079 --> 00:07:17,279
I've been pushing myself nonstop.

220
00:07:17,879 --> 00:07:18,959
I kept telling myself,

221
00:07:19,800 --> 00:07:21,519
as long as I do my job well,

222
00:07:22,040 --> 00:07:22,959
put in more effort,

223
00:07:23,160 --> 00:07:24,279
and work hard,

224
00:07:24,639 --> 00:07:25,439
at least I wouldn't

225
00:07:25,519 --> 00:07:26,560
end up worse off than everyone else.

226
00:07:27,240 --> 00:07:29,120
But look at me now. What am I doing?

227
00:07:29,759 --> 00:07:30,680
Sometimes I look down

228
00:07:30,680 --> 00:07:31,680
at myself,

229
00:07:32,319 --> 00:07:33,279
and I feel like

230
00:07:33,319 --> 00:07:34,839
a beast walking in circles,
turning a millstone.

231
00:07:35,920 --> 00:07:36,680
I'm 40 years old.

232
00:07:38,519 --> 00:07:39,720
I have no money.

233
00:07:39,879 --> 00:07:41,040
No career.

234
00:07:42,000 --> 00:07:43,720
I can't even have

235
00:07:45,279 --> 00:07:47,199
a child.

236
00:07:49,800 --> 00:07:51,439
What am I doing with my life?

237
00:07:56,560 --> 00:07:58,160
What do you mean "free time"?

238
00:07:58,600 --> 00:08:00,199
You let this whole group

239
00:08:00,199 --> 00:08:00,959
of seniors wander off,

240
00:08:01,000 --> 00:08:01,800
and didn't round them up?

241
00:08:02,199 --> 00:08:03,639
What if something happened?

242
00:08:03,879 --> 00:08:04,519
But nothing did.

243
00:08:05,319 --> 00:08:06,199
You photography club folks

244
00:08:06,240 --> 00:08:07,160
really are something.

245
00:08:07,160 --> 00:08:07,959
Impressive.

246
00:08:09,040 --> 00:08:09,839
Besides,

247
00:08:10,639 --> 00:08:11,720
if it's all free time,

248
00:08:11,839 --> 00:08:13,079
why do they need a tour guide?

249
00:08:13,639 --> 00:08:14,319
You're not guiding

250
00:08:14,519 --> 00:08:15,480
and still want to get paid?

251
00:08:15,839 --> 00:08:16,160
Fine.

252
00:08:16,399 --> 00:08:17,199
Maybe you can brush off

253
00:08:17,279 --> 00:08:18,120
one complaint,

254
00:08:18,160 --> 00:08:19,519
but a whole tour group?

255
00:08:19,720 --> 00:08:20,399
If they file a complaint

256
00:08:20,519 --> 00:08:21,600
with the tourism bureau,

257
00:08:21,759 --> 00:08:22,720
who's taking responsibility?

258
00:08:27,399 --> 00:08:27,759
Mr. Song.

259
00:08:29,240 --> 00:08:30,959
if I remember correctly,
last year there was a time

260
00:08:30,959 --> 00:08:32,120
when you personally led a tour.

261
00:08:32,159 --> 00:08:33,759
It was that
Ludao Island sightseeing tour.

262
00:08:33,840 --> 00:08:34,559
As I recall,

263
00:08:34,559 --> 00:08:36,200
you lost the whole group, didn't you?

264
00:08:36,240 --> 00:08:37,600
If I hadn't stepped in
and helped you out,

265
00:08:37,679 --> 00:08:39,279
how would you have handled that, huh?

266
00:08:40,480 --> 00:08:41,320
(VIP Ms. Wang)

267
00:08:41,559 --> 00:08:42,080
Ms. Wang.

268
00:08:42,200 --> 00:08:42,799
My VIP client.

269
00:08:45,320 --> 00:08:46,200
Sis!

270
00:08:46,320 --> 00:08:47,080
Yitong!

271
00:08:47,320 --> 00:08:48,000
Sis, what made you

272
00:08:48,000 --> 00:08:49,120
call me today?

273
00:08:49,360 --> 00:08:50,080
(VIP Ms. Wang)
This month,

274
00:08:50,120 --> 00:08:51,759
(VIP Ms. Wang)
I made over two million this month.

275
00:08:51,759 --> 00:08:52,879
That's amazing!

276
00:08:53,000 --> 00:08:54,200
Why do you always rub it in?

277
00:08:54,279 --> 00:08:54,720
I almost

278
00:08:54,759 --> 00:08:55,879
forgot my problems.

279
00:08:55,960 --> 00:08:56,799
I'd forgotten I was broke.

280
00:08:56,799 --> 00:08:57,279
Then you called,

281
00:08:57,279 --> 00:08:58,080
and now I remember.

282
00:08:58,120 --> 00:08:59,120
You're so annoying.

283
00:08:59,480 --> 00:09:00,960
Making money is easy.

284
00:09:01,159 --> 00:09:02,879
But I can't even spend it all.

285
00:09:03,000 --> 00:09:03,840
Every day I'm out

286
00:09:03,879 --> 00:09:05,039
with my girlfriends,

287
00:09:05,320 --> 00:09:06,600
for good food and drinks.

288
00:09:06,600 --> 00:09:08,519
If you can't spend it all,
give me a call, okay?

289
00:09:08,639 --> 00:09:10,000
